==English==

{{rank|provided|Rome|twelve|971|opposite|vast|isn't|board}}

===Etymology===
{{L.}} [[oppositus]] from [[opponere]], ''to [[oppose]]''

===Pronunciation===
* ([[RP]]) {{IPA| /ˈɒpəzɪt/}}
*{{audio|en-us-opposite.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Adjective===
'''opposite'''
# [[located]] [[directly]] [[across]] from something else, or from each other
#:''It was in the '''opposite''' hand.''
# [[facing]] the other [[way]]
#:''They were moving in '''opposite''' directions.''
# of either of two [[complementary]] or [[mutually]] [[exclusive]] things
#:''They were of the '''opposite''' sex.''
